    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require councils to check all deceased cats for microchips before disposal",
        "additional_details": "Mandatory microchipping of cats becomes law this year(2024).\r\n \r\nMany vets and animal welfare organisations scan cats for microchips. We want ALL councils to be required to do the same for any deceased cat.\r\n \r\nPeople pay up to \u00a330 per cat to microchip them, to help reunification, but currently a deceased cat can be disposed of without needing to check if he/she is chipped, or trying to reunite them with their companion/owner!\r\n \r\nWe believe this is not acceptable.\r\n",
        "background": "We want mandatory microchip checks for EVERY cat - whether obviously domestic or feral - found deceased on any street or property or land, by EVERY council in England.",
